11/05/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi said on Monday (May 10th) that he wants a judiciary that functions independently of politics. Speaking at a meeting to mark National Day of Justice, Topi reminded judges and prosecutors of the importance of independence in decision-making processes. "More efforts need to be made against corruption, and your actions need to be professional and based on ethics," Topi said. Also attending the event were international community representatives, including OSCE chief in Tirana Robert Bosch. (Lajmifundit, Shekulli, Top Channel, TVSH, Alsat - 10/05/10)
